"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-04-25-ready-paris-hold-2024-olympic-games-20716292\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Bed bugs.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 9, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Faecal matter-riddled rivers.\", \"from\": 10, \"to\": 39, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Transport disruption caused by striking workers.\", \"from\": 40, \"to\": 88, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Security concerns.The Moulin Rouge windmill has no sails.\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 111, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.120233026639872e-35, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It'sParis, ready to host the 2024 Olympic and Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 194, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999798104136918, \"rank\": 1.1885912999246854e-05, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympic andParalympicGames will be held in less than 100 days in theFrench capital.\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The games begin on July 26, with the men's and women's football and rugby games kicking off two days before, with the Paralympic Games to follow from August 28 until September 8.\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yetpollssuggest French people are not in the Olympic spirit.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most French people are indifferent at best to the games (36%), with 27% worrying, 23% satisfied, 12% enthusiastic and 5% just 'angry'.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 553, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Leon Davis, a senior lecturer in marketing and events management at Teesside University in Middlesbrough, does not blame the French for not being too buzzed.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Davis_(footballer)\", \"score\": 0.9999986323446395, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leon Davis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13414980\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Davis_(footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leon_Davis_(footballer)\"}, {\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teesside_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teesside University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teesside_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teesside_University\"}, {\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middlesbrough\", \"score\": 0.9999997208451922, \"rank\": 2.7915466585979783e-07, \"text\": \"Middlesbrough\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middlesbrough\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middlesbrough\"}, {\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9500651648435159, \"rank\": 0.05255737500327751, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Understandably, some will doubt the city's preparedness,\\u00a0given the\\u00a0sail\\u00a0of one of the most famous Parisian landmarks, the Moulin Rouge, toppled off,' he said.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.120233026639872e-35, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's not uncommon for cities to race against the clock, and Paris has been planning the event for a number of years so we all expect it to be ready in time.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1068, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of the biggest worries about the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They never quite walked down the runway, butParis Fashion Week in September saw something rather unlikely begin trending: bed bugs.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Fashion_Week\", \"score\": 0.9632675946985442, \"rank\": 0.038133126769660936, \"text\": \"Fashion Week\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Fashion_Week\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Fashion_Week\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were seen riding the Paris Metro, catching the latest film at cinemas, dining at high-end restaurants and crawling around Charles de Gaulle airport.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"score\": 0.9999998407884176, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Metro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ANSES, agovernmenthealth agency,found that one in 10 French householdshad experienced bedbugs between 2017 and 2022.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ANSES\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ANSES\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ANSES\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ANSES\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  In its report, the agency said: 'The upsurge in bed-bug infestations in recent years has been due in particular to the rise in travel and the increasing resistance of bed bugs to insecticides.'\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8117726429110883e-25, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 1746, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.445789010335684e-22, \"text\": \"HTML5\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With travel being one reason for the rise in the blood-suckers, Paris' tourism office estimates thatclose to 16,000,000 peoplecould visit the region during July-September.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ask any swimmer what they'd prefer to swim in, clean water or a river riddled with 'faecal matter', we can take a guess which they'd prefer.\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this is the question facing Olympic athletes dreaming of taking home the gold in sports such as marathon swimming or triathlon in only two weeks.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If everything goes to plan, athletes will take a dip in the Seine - the river that has been illegal to swim in for a century due to high pollution levels.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2497, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 1.0378449851270746e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A little thing called the marquee opening ceremony will also take place along the river, rather than at the usual Olympic Stadium.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France has spent 1.4billion euros to clean the river that runs through the heart of the capital and upgrade its creaky sewage systems for next Spring.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999923332328, \"rank\": 7.611913096064946e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The biggest issue will be the Seine, and whether it will be ready for the opening ceremony, especially as it will break tradition for the first time by not being held at the stadium,' added Dr Davis.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 3077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2908, \"end\": 2913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 1.0378449851270746e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French nonprofit Surfriderhas found'concentrations of enterococci and E. coli' in the river this year.\", \"from\": 3079, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9500651648435159, \"rank\": 0.05255737500327751, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Recent tests have, however, shown improvement.\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris City Hall said the last week of June saw four days when the water was clean enough to swim in by European standards.\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rain could also pose a problem.\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the competition to start on July 26, rain could cause sewage to overflow.\", \"from\": 3396, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials expect it to be sunny and dry for the Olympics, however, and that the sun's UV rays could kill off any bacteria - a literal ray of hope.\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organising the Olympics is a marathon in and of itself, something that requires a heap of staff to pull off.\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What does not help is when these staff go on strike.\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Major trade unionsfighting for better pay amid inflation and against the now-increased retirement agehave warned of strike action, fearful of longer working hours, postponed holidays and a lack of childcare.\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organisers chose July 26 to August 11 for the competition as that's when countless Parisians leave for their sacrosanct summer holidays, easing pressure off the city's transit network.\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Public sector workers, from hospital andtransport workersto police officers and even those working at the French national mint, which makes the medals for the Game, have not been too pleased about that.\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4296, \"end\": 4302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9500651648435159, \"rank\": 0.05255737500327751, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Security guards arethe latest to threaten strike action, while industrial action from airport staff was avoided after bosses agreed to bonuses.\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some hospital staff arerefusing to clock inon the opening of the Olympics over working conditions.\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the Olympics' top organisers in Paris toldRTLthat organisers will not ban people from striking 'to defend their rights', which is as French of a response as you can get.\", \"from\": 4638, \"to\": 4814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4677, \"end\": 4682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of, it's not just the thought of transport staff walking out that could impact how smoothly the Olympics go.\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 4933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several key exertions to the Paris Metro station that are part of the 'Grand Paris Express' are complete or underway.\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 5052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4964, \"end\": 4975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"score\": 0.9999998407884176, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Metro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though the rest will not be ready until 2030, transit officials have said most lines do not service Olympic sites.\", \"from\": 5053, \"to\": 5167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Charles de Gaulle expressway,\\u00a0which will link\\u00a0the airport and the Gare de l'Est railway station, will not be ready, however.\", \"from\": 5169, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless of what Metro, bus, trams and suburb train lines are running, all will cost double what they normally do over the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5299, \"to\": 5433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00cele-de-France Mobilit\\u00e9s, the local authority in charge of public transport companies,\\u00a0said this was needed so locals would not have to solely bear the cost of the influx of riders.\", \"from\": 5435, \"to\": 5615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they will have plenty of options.\", \"from\": 5617, \"to\": 5654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"City officials hope to add 10,000 more bikes across some 60 'Olympistes' - cycle routes with getting between Olympic venues in mind.\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is aiming to carry out the Olympics with 50% less planet-warming carbon emissions compared to London 2012 and Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5789, \"end\": 5794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5889, \"end\": 5900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.311566222751923e-13, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris was already on edge after a string of bomb hoaxes in October - a threat fromISIS-affiliated groups against a Champions League Gamethe city was hosting earlier this month did not help.\", \"from\": 5916, \"to\": 6105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5916, \"end\": 5921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6031, \"end\": 6047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.483901610736562e-39, \"text\": \"Champions League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's interior minister, G\\u00e9rald\\u00a0Darmanin, said an 'anti-terrorist' perimeter will be set up around the Seine one week before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 6107, \"to\": 6256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6107, \"end\": 6113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999923332328, \"rank\": 7.611913096064946e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6213, \"end\": 6218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 1.0378449851270746e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only authorised traffic will be allowed to flow through - residents will need special QR codes to come and go - and several Metro and tram stops will shut.\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But as Dr Davis says, since Paris was handed hosting rights in 2017, conflict has come to define the following years.\", \"from\": 6415, \"to\": 6532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6443, \"end\": 6448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the Russia-Ukraine war and the Covid pandemic to the violence that has seized Parisian streets in recent years.\", \"from\": 6533, \"to\": 6649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6542, \"end\": 6560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russia-Ukraine war\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russo-Ukrainian_War\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'All these factors do not seem enough to prevent a successful summer of games,' he stressed.\", \"from\": 6651, \"to\": 6743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zoe Adjey, a senior lecturer in hospitality and tourism at the University of East London, told Metro.co.uk how a list of potential problems like the above is almost a guarantee when it comes to organising something as elaborate as the Olympics.\", \"from\": 6745, \"to\": 6989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6745, \"end\": 6748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"score\": 0.8150257872198072, \"rank\": 0.2238010779517793, \"text\": \"Zoe\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\"}, {\"begin\": 6840, \"end\": 6851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AndLondon knows all about that.\", \"from\": 6991, \"to\": 7022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'In 2012, as London prepared to host the Olympics and Paralympics, a series of negative stories emerged in the months leading up to the events, which some felt would ruin the Olympics,' she said.\", \"from\": 7024, \"to\": 7219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7037, \"end\": 7043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999481588, \"rank\": 5.155270998099636e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'One such scandal was the G4S debacle,' Adjey said, referring to the private security company that, only a month before the opening ceremony, admitted it would not be able to provide enough staff.\", \"from\": 7221, \"to\": 7417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The media was also filled with negativity surrounding sponsors like McDonald's and Coca-Cola, criticising them for promoting junk food.\", \"from\": 7419, \"to\": 7555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7503, \"end\": 7512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.999999756109021, \"rank\": 2.43891147291647e-07, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'However, it is important to remember the moment when Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II and James Bond parachuted into the Olympic Stadium in Stratford - at that instant, every one of those negative stories dissipated.'\", \"from\": 7557, \"to\": 7773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7611, \"end\": 7641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9734563619629713e-55, \"text\": \"Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 7623, \"end\": 7641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.302891208417325e-12, \"text\": \"Queen Elizabeth II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 7629, \"end\": 7641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1397009945539655e-16, \"text\": \"Elizabeth II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 7646, \"end\": 7656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"score\": 0.9999934934678768, \"rank\": 6.506574130710171e-06, \"text\": \"James Bond\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond\"}, {\"begin\": 7696, \"end\": 7705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"score\": 0.8943832809785329, \"rank\": 0.11808887789914158, \"text\": \"Stratford\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stratford_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"London and Paris have a track record of staging successful events that bring planetary attention to them - and Paris 2024 will be one of them.\", \"from\": 7775, \"to\": 7917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7775, \"end\": 7781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999481588, \"rank\": 5.155270998099636e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 7786, \"end\": 7791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090223790884818e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7886, \"end\": 7896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.051822029609206e-26, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Instead of focusing on potential problems,' Adjey added, 'we should recognise the logistical marvel of executing an event of this magnitude and celebrate the Olympians who are currently training to deliver the performances of their lives.'\", \"from\": 7919, \"to\": 8159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get in touch with our news team by emailing us atwebnews@metro.co.uk.\", \"from\": 8161, \"to\": 8230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8218, \"end\": 8229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our news page.\", \"from\": 8232, \"to\": 8279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:France accused of 'shameful' decision days before Paris Olympics  ArrowMORE:Rafael Nadal makes retirement decision after beating Bjorn Borg's son in Bastad  ArrowMORE:'She's not the wicked stepmother': How Queen Camilla won over her critics  Stay on top of the headlines with daily email updates.\", \"from\": 8281, \"to\": 8587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8291, \"end\": 8297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999923332328, \"rank\": 7.611913096064946e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 8367, \"end\": 8379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia